Durban - A man who robbed a butchery in July 2017 has been jailed for 15 years. This week the Eshowe Regional Court in Eshowe sentenced 34-year-old Nkosinathi Mhuqu Cele to 15 years imprisonment. He was found guilty of armed robbery. According to KwaZulu Natal police spokesman Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane the victim and his colleague, had just cashed up and locked the butchery on July 21, just after 5 pm when they were accosted by Cele. At gunpoint, Cele took an undisclosed amount of cash and fled. A case of robbery was opened at Eshowe police station for investigation. "Following a rigorous investigation, detectives were led the to Nkanini in Eshowe where the suspect was arrested. He was later positively identified by the victims during an identification parade." Zwane said Cele made several court appearances until his sentencing. He said they welcomed the sentence and hopes this sends a message to would-be offenders that they will face the full might of the law. DAILY NEWS